# Bug #32 NEGATIVE fixture: a FLAT (`@unboxed`) Type param on a BOXED `enum`, then a BOXED
# instantiation (`Box[Int]`). The flat (tflt) param vs boxed (tbox) datatype is a latent sort
# inconsistency our lowering used to emit. The frontend now NORMALIZES the flat Type param to
# boxed on a boxed datatype (matching the pinned "@unboxed enum lowers boxed" policy), so the
# emitted L2 is consistently sorted and the TYPECHECKER handles it gracefully (no crash; it
# reaches the nerror line). Asserts: the frontend does NOT crash the type passes on this shape.
enum Box[A: Type @unboxed]:
    case Mk(A)

def f(b: Box[Int]) -> Int:
    0
